Same here. Using tensorflow 0.12 and master (self-compiled from git and the release .whl from the tensorflow installation guide), I get this error when trying to use inceptionv3 after putting it through optimize_for_inference.py.

It can be worked-around, however, by using 0.12rc1 from the nightly builds which solved the problem for now.

body:
Same here. Using tensorflow 0.12 and master (self-compiled from git and the release .whl from the tensorflow installation guide), I get this error when trying to use inceptionv3 after putting it through [optimize_for_inference.py](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/tools/optimize_for_inference.py).

It can be worked-around, however, by using [0.12rc1](https://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Nightly/job/nightly-matrix-linux-gpu/TF_BUILD_IS_OPT=OPT,TF_BUILD_IS_PIP=PIP,TF_BUILD_PYTHON_VERSION=PYTHON3.5,label=gpu-linux/) from the nightly builds which solved the problem for now.
